---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';

export const prerender = true;
---

<Layout 
  title="Terms of Service - Track Your Labs"
  description="Terms and conditions for using Track Your Labs services."
>
  <main class="flex-1 px-6 md:px-8 lg:px-10 pb-6 md:pb-8 lg:pb-10 pt-20 max-w-4xl mx-auto">
    <div class="prose prose-gray max-w-none">
      <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-4">Terms of Service</h1>
      
      <p class="text-sm mb-2"><strong>Last Updated:</strong> August 12, 2025</p>
      <p class="text-sm mb-2"><strong>Company:</strong> Snowflake Health, LLC ("Snowflake Health," "we," "us," or "our")</p>
      <p class="text-sm mb-6"><strong>Service:</strong> Track Your Labs – <a href="https://www.trackyourlabs.com/" class="text-blue-600 hover:underline">https://www.trackyourlabs.com/</a></p>
      
      <hr class="my-8" />
      
      <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mt-6 mb-2">TL;DR – What You Need to Know</h3>
      <ul class="list-disc pl-5 mt-2">
        <li>You can anonymously upload lab files—no account or personal info required.</li>
        <li>No testing packages or payments are being offered at this time.</li>
        <li>The tool is processing-only—lab results vanish once the session ends.</li>
        <li>Not a replacement for medical care—just a private, HIPAA-compliant way to view your labs.</li>
        <li>Any legal disputes are handled via arbitration in Texas, unless you opt out.</li>
        <li>Future Terms changes will come with advance notice.</li>
      </ul>
      
      <hr class="my-8" />
      
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mt-8 mb-4">Overview</h2>
      <p>
        These Terms of Service ("Terms") govern your access to and use of Track Your Labs ("Services"). By using the anonymous lab-upload tool on our website, you agree to these Terms. If you do <strong>not</strong> agree, please do not use the Services.
      </p>
      
      <hr class="my-8" />
      
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mt-8 mb-4">1. Service Description</h2>
      <ul class="list-disc pl-5 mt-2">
        <li><strong>Anonymous Lab Upload Tool:</strong> You can upload up to 50 lab files (PDFs or images) anonymously—no sign-up or personal information required.</li>
        <li><strong>HIPAA-Compliant Processing:</strong> Your data is processed securely but is <strong>not stored</strong>. It vanishes when you close the page.</li>
        <li><strong>Optional Waitlist:</strong> Only if you choose to join, you may provide your email so we can notify you when full, account-based features are available. This is entirely optional and separate from anonymous uploads.</li>
      </ul>
      
      <hr class="my-8" />
      
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mt-8 mb-4">2. What We Don't Offer or Do</h2>
      <ul class="list-disc pl-5 mt-2">
        <li><strong>No paid testing packages or subscriptions</strong> are currently available—those details are placeholders in the legacy version of this policy.</li>
        <li><strong>We are not a medical provider.</strong> The tool is for informational use only and does not replace medical advice.</li>
      </ul>
      
      <hr class="my-8" />
      
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mt-8 mb-4">3. No User Accounts Yet</h2>
      <ul class="list-disc pl-5 mt-2">
        <li>There is <strong>no account registration</strong>, password, or billing required for using the anonymous tool.</li>
        <li>If you join the waitlist, only your email is stored for notification purposes.</li>
      </ul>
      
      <hr class="my-8" />
      
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mt-8 mb-4">4. Disclaimers & Eligibility</h2>
      <ul class="list-disc pl-5 mt-2">
        <li>You must be 18 years or older and reside in the U.S. to participate—especially if or when account-based features are introduced.</li>
        <li>Use the uploaded results responsibly—<strong>this tool is not a substitute for professional medical advice</strong>.</li>
      </ul>
      
      <hr class="my-8" />
      
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mt-8 mb-4">5. Dispute Resolution & Governing Law</h2>
      <ul class="list-disc pl-5 mt-2">
        <li>These Terms are governed by the laws of the State of Texas. Any disputes will be resolved via <strong>binding arbitration in Austin, Texas</strong>, unless you opt out within 30 days of consenting.</li>
      </ul>
      
      <hr class="my-8" />
      
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mt-8 mb-4">6. Changes to the Terms</h2>
      <ul class="list-disc pl-5 mt-2">
        <li>If we update these Terms, we'll notify you—either by email if you're on the waitlist, or via in-site notice—<strong>at least 30 days before</strong> the changes take effect. Continued use after the update means you agree to the new Terms.</li>
      </ul>
      
      <hr class="my-8" />
      
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mt-8 mb-4">7. Contact Us</h2>
      <p>If you have any questions or need help:</p>
      <p><strong>Snowflake Health, LLC</strong></p>
      <p>Email: <strong>legal@trackyourlabs.com</strong> or <strong>privacy@trackyourlabs.com</strong></p>
      <p>Website: <a href="https://www.trackyourlabs.com/" class="text-blue-600 hover:underline">https://www.trackyourlabs.com/</a></p>
    </div>
  </main>
  
  <Footer />
</Layout>

<style>
  .prose {
    max-width: none;
  }
  
  .prose table {
    width: 100%;
  }
  
  .prose blockquote {
    font-style: normal;
  }
</style>